your code will fail in corner cases but you need to find at least the right placeholder for the total 


number of chunks =  message length / 160 +1
we need to take care of place holder (how many digits (number of chunks) )
corner cases  1 place holders with value 9 will be 2 placeHolder 
corner cases  2 place holders with value 99 will be 3 placeHolder 
corner cases  3 place holders with value 999 will be 4 placeHolder 
....
input size 

getPlaceHolder (int n ){
if (n < 9) return 1;
if (n>9 && n < 100) return 2;
if (n>99 && n < 1000) return 3;
if (n>999&& n < 10000) return 4;
}

then you can build your string list as you did

I got this question in my OA. Of course I couldn't come up with the solution during the interview. Here is the implementation I did later for this question.
But it's **O(n!)**

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        String input = "I know you can ...";
        String[] words = input.split(" ");
        List<String> lines = getLines(words, 1, 160);
        for (String line : lines) {
            System.out.println("length: " + line.length() + " Text: " + line);
        }
    } 

    private static List<String> getLines(String[] words, int divider, int limit) {

        if (words.length == 0) {
            return new ArrayList<>();
        }

        List<String> lines = new ArrayList<>();
        int lineNumber = 1;
        int cursor = 0;
        while (cursor < words.length && lineNumber <= divider) {
            StringBuilder line = new StringBuilder();
            int suffixLength = getNumberLength(lineNumber) + 3 + getNumberLength(divider);
            while (cursor < words.length && line.length() + suffixLength <= limit) {
                line.append(words[cursor++]).append(" ");
            }
            if ((line.length() + suffixLength) > limit) {
                String newLine = line.substring(0, line.lastIndexOf(" "));
                newLine = newLine.substring(0, newLine.lastIndexOf(" ") + 1);
                line = new StringBuilder().append(newLine);
                cursor--;
            }
            line.append("(" + lineNumber + "/" + divider + ")");
            lines.add(line.toString());
            lineNumber++;
        }

        if ((words.length - 1) > cursor) {
            return getLines(words, divider + 1, limit);
        }

        return lines;
    }

    private static int getNumberLength(int i) {
        int length = 0;

        while (i > 0) {
            i /= 10;
            length++;
        }

        return length;
    }
